1. There are many ways to run Python!
2. Later on we'll explore the difference between running a Python .py script or running a Python code in a notebook enviornment
Either way, we will still want to install Python!

# Installation Lecture:
1. Install Anaconda Distribution for Python.
        Anaconda installs Python and an easy to use development enviornment and navigator launch tool
2. Briefly run Jupyter Notebook
3. Explore "no install" online options

Quick Note:
•	There are now many online "no install" Python enviornments that can run in the browser (as long as you have an internet connection)
•	While not officially part of the course, we will give you a brief tour of these online "no install" options at the end.
Installation Guide:
•	To Install Python we will use the free Individual Anaconda distribution.

•	This distribution includes Python as well as many other useful libraries, including Jupyter Notebook environment.

•	Anaconda can also easily be installed on to any major OS, Windows, MacOS, or Linux.


Step-1:  To Begin Go to 

https://www.anaconda.com/downloads

 

Step-2: When you click on Downloads It will take you to Anaconda Installers section

Depending on Windows or MacOS click on Python 3.x latest version
 

•	Since I am using Windows click on 64bit graphical installer

Click on 64bit installer

Destination Folder: C:\Users\Arahanth\anaconda3


